description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting senior admin post is available in the field of clinical research. The Clinical Research Network is the clinical research delivery arm of the NHS. The network operates nationally across NHS England through a national coordinating centre and 15 local branches delivering research in the NHS across all disease areas. The NIHR Clinical Research Network: Thames Valley and South Midlands (LCRN) is hosted by Oxford University Hospitals NHS Trust. Clinical research is delivered through 6 Divisions within the network, covering a total of 30 disease-specific Specialty Groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The overall function of the Divisional Support Officer is to provide an effective administrative support service for across the following specialties: Dementias and Neurodegeneration, Mental Health, Neurological Disorders, Ageing. The majority of the Divisional Support Officer’s time will be spent on work relating to research and development. The post holder will need to manage their own workload effectively, undertake project work as necessary and will be expected to support and liaise with all the CRN team members within their specialties across the network geography.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 8th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planned Interview Date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held remotely by videoconferencing or face to face depending on trust policy at the time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal discussion contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Collins, Research Delivery Manager on Helen.Collins@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
